## Module 1 — `thresholds.py` (Data-Calibrated)

All thresholds are derived from your **Severity Detection Features** document, cross-validated against the **actual data ranges** observed in `telemetry_metrics.csv`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Thresholds below are calibrated to **your data** (not the generic examples in the prompt).  
> Raw data ranges: cpu max=100, heap max=769MB, p99 max=2036ms, db_p99 max=1517ms, error_rate max=85%, queue_lag max=457.

| Feature | Normal (no flag) | Warning Threshold | Critical Threshold | Data Basis |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `cpu_utilization` | < 70% | ≥ 70% | ≥ 90% | Max=100, 75th pct=51.8 |
| `memory_utilization` | < 0.75 | ≥ 0.75 | ≥ 0.90 | Max=0.44, scaled to fraction |
| `heap_mb` | < 2470 MB (65%) | ≥ 2470 MB | ≥ 3420 MB (90%) | Configured max=3800MB per generator |
| `gc_pause_p99` | < 100 ms | ≥ 100 ms | ≥ 400 ms | Max=650, 75th=26.9 |
| `p99_latency` | < 500 ms | ≥ 500 ms | ≥ 2000 ms | Max=2036, mean=365 |
| `p95_latency` | < 300 ms | ≥ 300 ms | ≥ 1200 ms | Max=1932 |
| `db_p99` | < 200 ms | ≥ 200 ms | ≥ 1000 ms | Max=1517, mean=95 |
| `disk_write_latency` | < 200 ms | ≥ 200 ms | ≥ 600 ms | Max=545 |
| `disk_read_latency` | < 50 ms | ≥ 50 ms | ≥ 150 ms | Max=444 |
| `error_rate` | < 5% | ≥ 5% | ≥ 20% | Max=85%, mean=17.9% |
| `upstream_timeout_rate` | < 5% | ≥ 5% | ≥ 20% | Max=55% |
| `cache_miss_rate` | < 30% | ≥ 30% | ≥ 80% | Max=99%, mean=13.4% |
| `cache_hit_rate` | > 70% | ≤ 70% | ≤ 20% | **Lower = worse** |
| `queue_lag` | < 100 | ≥ 100 | ≥ 300 | Max=457, mean=53.7 |
| `thread_pool_queue` | < 15 | ≥ 15 | ≥ 40 | Max=514, mean=92 |
| `network_errors` | < 2/window | ≥ 2 | ≥ 10 | Max=38 |
| `retry_count_per_request` | < 1.5 | ≥ 1.5 | ≥ 3.0 | Max=0.9 (scaled 0–1 in data) |
| `active_connections` | < 150 (60% of 250) | ≥ 150 | ≥ 225 (90%) | Max=414, pool=250 |
| `db_connection_pool` | < 0.75 | ≥ 0.75 | ≥ 0.95 | Max=0.99 (fraction) |
| `circuit_breaker_state` | 0 (closed) | 1 (half-open) | 2 (open) | Categorical |
| `root_span_error_rate` | < 10% | ≥ 10% | ≥ 40% | Trace feature |
| `span_gap_ratio` | < 0.3 | ≥ 0.3 | ≥ 0.6 | Trace feature |
| `uniform_slowdown_score` | < 0.5 | ≥ 0.5 | ≥ 0.8 | Trace feature |
| `duplicate_trace_id_count` | ≤ 3 | > 3 | > 10 | Trace feature |
| `distinct_error_services` | ≤ 1 | > 1 | > 2 + growing | Trace feature |
| `log_max_severity` | < 2 | ≥ 2 (WARNING) | ≥ 4 (CRITICAL) | Log feature |
| `log_critical_count` | 0 | > 0 | > 2 | Log feature |
| `log_has_exception` | 0 | 1 | — (binary, warning only) | Log feature |

**Derived Features (computed inside engine):**
- `p99_minus_p50_ratio` = `p99_latency / p50_latency` — Warning: > 3×, Critical: > 8×
- `heap_growth_rate` = `heap_mb[t] - heap_mb[t-1]` — Warning: > 5 MB/cycle, Critical: > 20 MB/cycle
- `write_read_latency_ratio` = `disk_write_latency / disk_read_latency` — Warning: > 5×, Critical: > 15×

All thresholds are stored in `severity_config/thresholds.yaml` for easy modification.

